{"id":"clif_c_aclf","version":"0.0.1","templates":[{"id":"clif_c_aclf","version":"0.1.0"}],"language":"en","updated":"2021-08-26T21:22:25+02:00","authors":[{"name":"Núria Rodríguez Ruiz","email":"nuria.ruiz@cambio.se"}],"format":"CambioForm.v1","name":"clif_c_aclf","actions":[{"condition":"information_available.text == 'SpO2/FiO2 ratio'","assignments":["spo2/fio2_ratio.hidden = false"],"otherwise":["spo2/fio2_ratio.hidden = true"]},{"condition":"information_available.text == 'PaO2/FiO2 ratio'","assignments":["pao2/fio2_ratio.hidden = false"],"otherwise":["pao2/fio2_ratio.hidden = true"]}],"guidelines":[{"condition":"age && white_cell_count && bilirubin && creatinine && 'west-haven_grade_for_hepatic' && inr && map && information_available ","execution":[{"id":"CLIF_C_ACLF_guideline","version":"1"}]}],"elements":[{"type":"form","children":[{"type":"container","children":[{"type":"row","spanlarge":12,"spanmedium":8,"spansmall":4,"hidden":false,"readonly":false,"children":[{"type":"column","spanlarge":12,"spanmedium":8,"spansmall":4,"readonly":false,"hidden":false,"children":[{"text":"## CLIF-C ACLF (Acute-on-Chronic Liver Failure)\n\nCLIF-C ACLF score is used to predict the risk of 1-, 3-, 6- and 12- month mortality in acute-on-chronic liver failure patients.\n\nThe CLIF-C ACLF score formula is:\n\n\n\n- 10 x [0.33 x CLIF Organ Failure Score + 0.04 x age, years + 0.63 x ln(WBC count, 109 cells/L) - 2], where the CLIF Organ Failure Score is the sum of the points of all variables (organs/systems).\n\n\n\nThe probability of dying at a given time is:\n\n\n\n-  1 - e^y, where y = -CI x exp(β x CLIF-C ACLF score). Cl and β depend on the given time.","type":"text","size":"m","position":"left"}]},{"type":"column","spanlarge":8,"spanmedium":4,"spansmall":4,"hidden":false,"readonly":false,"children":[{"text":"Input","type":"text","size":"m","position":"left","readonly":true},{"type":"input-quantity","label":"Age","name":"age","unitoptions":[{"readonlyAttributes":["precision"],"u